Delicious! I cut my pitas into 6ths before toasting them. The combination of flavors is wonderful.

Rating: 1
I made this recipe for a cocktail party and it was barely touched. The look of it alone was enough to turn most people off. The mixture was this odd greenish-yellow, that I really hoped would look better as it cooked, but it did not. The taste was tangy and not at all interesting. I don't understand all the rave reviews.

Rating: 3
Made this for my first cocktail party and have to admit - was a little leary of it. I wanted to try something different and amazingly enough - the crowd loved this recipe. It was gone two minutes after I putting the serving plate out! Based on the below reviews, omitted the apricot preserves and not having tried it with - it tasted just fine. If you do not have the preserves on hand, don't make the effort to buy some - omit it.

